  <md:abstract><para>By the end of this section, you will be able to:</para>
<list>
<item>Explain why the hydrogen atom has magnetic properties</item>
<item>Explain why the energy levels of a hydrogen atom associated with orbital angular momentum are split by an external magnetic field</item>
<item>Use quantum numbers to calculate the magnitude and direction of the orbital magnetic dipole moment of a hydrogen atom</item>
</list></md:abstract>
  <md:language>en</md:language>
